{
  "texts": [
    "This score-based system is a significant departure from other frameworks such as Reflexion [32], Resolving Agents [33], or Chain of Thought [34] methods, which our preliminary studies found to be less effective.",
    "In these frameworks, chat models generate arguments for and against initial designs, often leading to random and selective \"improvements\".",
    "In contrast, scalar scoring by the VM in the TVDL provides a more definitive and effective method for identifying the most promising designs.A key difference between this work and the implementations by Cobe et al. and Lightman et al.",
    "is the non-fine-tuned nature of the VM.",
    "GPT-3.5-Turbo was found to be sufficiently effective for this application even without specific fine-tuning."
  ]
}